0 - Using the Snipping Tool Shortcut 1 - Go to the page that you want to screenshot.
Go to the page that you want to screenshot. Open the program or screen that you want to take a picture of, making sure that any windows or items that you don't want on-screen are out of the way. 2 - Press ⊞ Win+⇧ Shift+S.
Press ⊞ Win+⇧ Shift+S. Doing so will cause your screen to turn light-grey, and your mouse will turn into a crosshairs icon.; 3 - Select an area to screenshot.
Select an area to screenshot. Click and drag your mouse from the top-left corner of the area that you want to screenshot to the bottom-right corner.;
- For example, if you want to screenshot the entire screen, you'd click and drag your mouse from the top-left corner of the screen to the bottom-right corner of the screen. 4 - Release the mouse button.
Release the mouse button. This will both take a screenshot of your selected area and save it to your clipboard, from which point it can be pasted into any program that accepts pasted photos.;
